The '''Northern Illinois University shooting''' was an incident that took place on [[February 14]] [[2008]], during which a gunman shot multiple people on the campus of [[Northern Illinois University]] in [[DeKalb, Illinois]]; five of his victims were killed, eighteen were wounded. The incident happened on the campus's Cole Hall at approximately 3:05 p.m. local time.<ref name="campus_alert"/> The school placed the campus on lockdown and cancelled all classes until February 25. Students and teachers were advised to head to a secure location and take cover, avoiding the scene and all buildings in the vicinity of the area.<ref>{{cite news|title=Six Dead After University Shooting|url=http://www.citynews.ca/news/news_19625.aspx|publisher=[[CityNews]]|date=[[2008-02-14]] |accessdate=2008-02-14}}</ref> Six people died in the incident, including the perpetrator, making it the fourth-deadliest university shooting in United States history, after the [[Virginia Tech massacre]], the [[Charles Whitman|University of Texas Clock Tower shooting]], and the [[California State University, Fullerton library massacre]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FGCU pays tribute to Northern Illinois team|work=Scott Hotard|url=http://www.naplesnews.com/news/2008/feb/29/softball-fgcu-pays-tribute-northern-illinois-team/|publisher=Naples News|date=[[2008-02-29]]|accessdate=2008-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=3 p.m. update: Gunman identified in NIU shootings; 6 dead|url=http://www.daily-chronicle.com/articles/2008/02/15/news/latest_news/news01.txt|publisher=DeKalb Daily Chronicle|date=[[2008-02-15]]|accessdate=2008-04-11}}</ref>

==Shooting==
At approximately 3:06 pm CST, Steven Kazmierczak entered a large auditorium-style lecture hall in Cole Hall with 150 to 200 students. The door he used led directly to the stage in front of the classroom where Kazmierczak stood and fired into the crowd of students with a shotgun and three handguns; the shotgun was smuggled in using a guitar case and the handguns were concealed under his coat.<ref name="CNN_0214">{{cite news|title=18 shot, five dead including gunman, at Northern Illinois University|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/US/02/14/university.shooting/index.html|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=[[2008-02-14]] |accessdate=2008-02-14}}</ref><ref name="msnbc">{{cite news|author=Staff Writer|title=Gunman opens fire on Illinois campus|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/23171567/|publisher=[[MSNBC]]|date=[[2008-02-14]] |accessdate=2008-02-14}}</ref><ref name="ap_source">{{cite web|url=http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5i72zWlWRLvc1ejGI5WpefItEjKCAD8UQQGT81|title=7 Dead in N. Illinois U. Hall Shooting|work=Associated Press|date=2008-02-15|accessdate=2008-02-15}}</ref><ref name="CNN_0215">{{cite news|title= Source IDs alleged campus gunman who killed 6, himself|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/US/02/15/university.shooting/index.html|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=2008-02-15
|accessdate=2008-02-15}}</ref>  The gunman was a former NIU Sociology graduate student and a current graduate student in the school of [[social work]] at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]].<ref name="TribuneGunman">{{cite news |title=NIU noted gunman's scholarship |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/chi-shooterfeb15,0,2581284.story |publisher=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=[[2008-02-15]] |accessdate=2008-02-15}}</ref><ref name="msnbc" /><ref name="foxnews021408">{{cite news|title=Gunman Dead; More Than a Dozen Injured at Northern Illinois University|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,330730,00.html|publisher=[[Fox News]]|date=[[2008-02-14]] |accessdate=2008-02-14}}</ref>   NIU Police Chief Donald Grady described him  as  "an outstanding student" who reportedly stopped taking medication recently and became "somewhat erratic".<ref name="ESPN.com"/>

A total of 24 people were shot, six of whom died (including the perpetrator, who shot himself before police arrived).<ref name="CNN_0214"/><ref name="foxnews021408">{{cite news|title=Gunman Dead; More Than a Dozen Injured at Northern Illinois University|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,330730,00.html|publisher=[[Fox News]]|date=[[2008-02-14]] |accessdate=2008-02-14}}</ref><ref name="chictribune">{{cite news|first=Jason|last=Meisner|title=NIU shooting leaves 6 dead|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/chi-niu-gunman_webfeb15,0,1760508.story|publisher=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=[[2008-02-14]] |accessdate=2008-02-14}}</ref> One witness reported that at least 30 shots were fired by the gunman; police later collected 48 shell casings and 6 shotgun shells.<ref name="NPRGunman">{{cite news|title=Illinois School Gunman Named; Toll Corrected |url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=19073647 |publisher=[[National Public Radio]] |date=[[2008-02-15]] |accessdate=2008-02-15}}</ref> By February 15, at least seven of the victims were in critical condition, one in good condition, one in stable and eight discharged, according to Kishwaukee Community Hospital.<ref name="Kishhospital">"[http://kishhospital.org/updates.html Kishwaukee Community Hospital update]."  Retrieved on [[February 15]] [[2008]].</ref> Two of the wounded were transferred by helicopter to [[Rockford, Illinois|Rockford]]'s [[OSF Saint Anthony Medical Center|Saint Anthony Medical Center]], three to [[Downers Grove, Illinois|Downers Grove's]] [[Advocate Good Samaritan Hospital|Good Samaritan Hospital]], and one to Rockford Memorial Hospital.<ref name="CNN_0214"/><ref name="Kishhospital"/> Two patients that had been hospitalized died as a result of their injuries.<ref name="chictribune"/> By 4:00 pm CST, school officials announced that there was no further danger and that [[counselor]]s would be made available in all [[residence hall]]s.<ref name="CNN_0214"/>

===Deceased===
A total of six people, all residents of [[Illinois]], were killed in the incident:<ref name="ESPN.com">{{cite news|title=NIU sporting events cancelled in wake of shooting|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/US/02/15/university.shooting/index.html|publisher=[[CNN.com]]|date=[[2008-02-15]] |accessdate=2008-02-15}}</ref><ref name="cnn.com-2">{{cite news|title= Gunman in Illinois campus shooting identified|url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/US/02/15/university.shooting/index.html|publisher=[[CNN.com]]|date=[[2008-02-15]] |accessdate=2008-02-15}}</ref>

* Gayle Dubowski, 20&nbsp;&mdash; [[Carol Stream, Illinois|Carol Stream]]
* Catalina Garcia, 20&nbsp;&mdash; [[Cicero, Illinois|Cicero]]
* Julianna Gehant, 32&nbsp;&mdash; [[Meriden, Illinois|Meriden]]
* Ryanne Mace, 19&nbsp;&mdash; [[Carpentersville, Illinois|Carpentersville]]
* Daniel Parmenter, 20&nbsp;&mdash; [[Elmhurst, Illinois|Elmhurst]]
* Steven Kazmierczak, 27&nbsp;&mdash; [[Champaign, Illinois|Champaign]] (perpetrator)

